As part of the application process, here we answer the questions posed for Google's Summer of Code.

   * 1.  Describe your organization.

[http://gobolinux.org GoboLinux] is a free software project which brings a [http://gobolinux.org/?page=at_a_glance unique organization] for the GNU/Linux file system hierarchy. The project started in 2002 as a Brazilian regional project, becoming an international community in a few months. Doing a lot of applied research, the development team aims to have a comprehensive set of ideas and tools that could be used as the foundation for a strong *NIX-based operating system.

   * 2. Why is your organization applying to participate in GSoC 2009? What do you hope to gain by participating?

The distribution grew up very fast in the past few years, and with many people thinking out of the box it's natural to have a few interesting projects in the to do list. This year the project collected some of the most promising ones and elected them as candidates to GSoC 2009, in the hope of bringing more talented developers to the team and helping the community as a whole with a new set of useful applications.

